==English==
===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''fæstnian'' "make fast, firm," also "ratify, betroth," from Proto-Germanic ''*fastinojanan'', from Proto-Indo-European base ''*past-'' "firm".

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|fasten||}}
#To [[attach]] or [[connect]] in a secure manner
#:''The sailor '''fastened''' the boat to the dock with a half-hitch.''

==German==
===Etymology===
Probably from and Indo-European root ''*pwos-to-'' "pure", related to Latin ''[[purus]]'' "pure" and Latin ''[[pius]]'' "pious".
===Verb===
'''fasten'''
# to [[fast]]
